Tung Huynh Minh is an Intern DevOps/Data Analytics professional with 0 years of commercial experience. Their core expertise lies in architectures such as OSI Model, TCP/IP Model, and techniques like Singular Value Decomposition, Collaborative Filtering, Machine Learning, and Deep Learning, using frameworks like PySpark. They have gained experience through various academic projects and internships, including a Network & Data Analyst Intern role at Ton Duc Thang University, where they applied theoretical knowledge to practical scenarios, focusing on network design, cybersecurity, data analytics, AI, and software development. Notably, they have worked on designing and deploying enterprise networks, configuring VLANs and VPNs, implementing Network Access Protection, and developing a recommendation system leveraging Singular Value Decomposition and Collaborative Filtering techniques.

